{
  "texts": [
    "Statement of the problem.",
    "In the previous few years there was a significant development in the pre-trained generative AI based on large language models (LLMs) with transformers and the services built upon them, OpenAI's ChatGPT, Google's Gemini, Anthropic's Claude, GitHub Copilot, Amazon CodeWhisperer and others.",
    "However, there remain several challenges and uncertainties regarding the effective integration of generative AI into software testing frameworks.",
    "This includes issues such as ensuring the reliability and accuracy of generated test cases, adapting AI algorithms to diverse software environments, and addressing ethical concerns surrounding autonomous testing systems.",
    "The following questions remain unanswered."
